# Mneme project/env-scoped memory example
#
# Use this with:
#   ./scripts/install.sh --profile project --env-file .env
#
# The installer will add MNEME_HOME automatically when needed.
# By default it uses:
#   ~/.local/share/mneme-memory-mcp/projects/<repo-name>
#
# To force memory into this repo checkout instead, uncomment:
# MNEME_HOME=.mneme
